def: Of or pertaining to the dead; as, mortuary monuments. Mortuaryurn, an urn for holding the ashes of the dead.
One who makes or practices contortions.
Any affection of the skin dependent on scrofula.
Trouble; distress; teen. [Obs.] "Cruel winter's tine." Spenser.
Custom, habit; usage. [R.]To observe this consuetude or law. Barnes.
That part of theological science directly preliminary to actualexegesis, or interpretation of the Scriptures.
